item.title: Check your PSA yearly guys
item.description: 6 weeks of radiation (not chemo) and harmone deprivation therapy. Another 9 months of HDT. PSA down to .11 compared to 13. AMA..to clarify the prostate is still there, a bit crispy now though, the cancer is gone. The process for me was this; Step 1 PSA yearly until it doubled to 13. Step 2: MRI with contrast to check it out and visualize it, confirm cancer. Step 3: Biopsy it, also insert gold implants on the prostate and hydro gel near rectum. Step 4: Pet Scan with contrast to further identify where the cancer is. Step 5: Initial visit to radiology for fitting of the leg holder, get 3 tattoo dots for laser cross hairs. First HDT injection. HDT injections every three months. Step 6: Radiation treatments, 6 weeks 5 x a week, it only takes about 3 - 5 min on the table. Used up PTO, had to put in FMLA paperwork to cover all the time off. Step 7: PSA test a few weeks after last radiation treatment. Dr. orders DNA test on biopsy sample to see if it was hereditary and plan HDT accordingly. Step 8: Post on Imgur Radiation and hydro gel Side effects: Frequent bathroom visits, 4-5 a night. pee/poop/pee every trip. peeing a lot during day too Life HDT side effects: MENopause weight gain, 15 lb so far crabbier tired/fatigue smoother skin

item.title: RIP Bean Machine
item.description: It’s Wednesday, my spoods, but I have sad news. The hardest part of keeping jumping spiders as pets is how short a time we get with them. I found Bean (regal jumping spider/phiddipus regius) curled in the bottom of his enclosure and instantly knew he’d passed. He’s almost a year and a half old (the max lifespan for males) so it’s not entirely surprising. But he had still been so vibrant and lively, that I didn’t really think his time was close. I got him as a bitty i6. He had the deepest, midnight blue chels and was always a curious little dude. Jumping spiders must be housed separately, otherwise they will cannibalize each other. But any time Bean got a glimpse of the ladies in their enclosures, he’d do his little dance to woo them. They never really took notice (they are my kind of ladies, after all). His loss is sad, but I was lucky to have been able to keep him for as long as I did. He brought so much joy to my life and I am grateful. I placed him in the soil of my Monstera to rest. To love a jumping spider is a gift. To love a creature that most people consider undesirable changes the way we think of love. To love this creature, knowing that grief is never far off, is a challenge that grows the soul and the ability to see love in unexpected ways and places. Rest easy, Bean.

item.title: Heads up for those who use Vyvanse
item.description:
Source: https://www.health.com/adhd-medication-recall-november-2025-11842155 FDA notice: https://www.accessdata.fda.gov/scripts/ires/?Product=216857
(I am posting the text instead of the screenshots because I can’t take good ones of these sections, sorry about that) FTA: Sun Pharmaceutical Industries recalled the medication due to “failed dissolution specifications,” meaning the drug did not dissolve as expected in laboratory settings, which could make it less effective. What You Should Do The manufacturer did not issue a press release about this recall, so there are no specific instructions for medication users. However, it’s not recommended to stop ADHD medication abruptly, as it could cause withdrawal symptoms. Check your medications at home, and if you have any bottles affected by the recall, don’t take them. Instead, contact your healthcare provider or pharmacy for guidance on obtaining a replacement bottle or refund.

item.title: Map of Indigenous American nations, c.1500s (Public domain, copyright-free)
item.description: From the author, PeterVexillographer on reddit: Yá'át'ééh everyone! This is a map I designed to show the traditional territories of the Indigenous nations of middle North America in their approximate 16th-century locations. Most similar maps place each nation in the area where each first European encounter occurred; but I wanted one that was set at a more specific time, and one that promoted a less colonial perspective - no hard border lines, and emphasizing Native names. After a couple years of researching, drawing, and revising, here is the first edition of my map. I did my best to make it as complete as possible, and to confirm all information in multiple sources, but there are surely many knowledge gaps that still need to be filled. Corrections are most welcome if you have any to offer. My hope is that this map will find its way to those more skilled than myself in Indian Country who can make it much more accurate and complete. So, I've released the entire project copyright-free into the public domain; anyone may copy, modify, or expand upon it in any way. Full HD downloads and GIS shapefiles available here. My wish is to share this continent's rich history in a way that can give context to our settler neighbors while lifting Indigenous pride. I hope you enjoy browsing the map. :) https://www.reddit.com/r/IndianCountry/comments/svz9gy/map_of_indigenous_american_nations_c1500s_public/
